2\sin(x)\cos(x)
3\sin(x)-4\sin^3(x)
\begin{align} 2\sin\left(1.5x\right)\cos\left(1.5x\right)&=2\sin \left(\frac{3x}{2}\right)\cos\left(\frac{3x}{2}\right)\\ \\ &=\sin(3x)\\ \\ &=\sin(x+2x)=\sin x \cos 2x+\sin2x\cos x\\ &=\sin x(1-2\sin^2 x)+2\sin x \cos^2 x\\ &=\sin x(1-2\sin^2 x)+2\sin x (1-\sin^2 x)\\ &=\sin x-2\sin^3 x+2\sin x-2\sin^3 x\\ &=3\sin x-4\sin^3 x \quad \quad \quad\quad \quad \quad\quad \quad \quad\quad \quad \quad \text{Q.E.D} \end{align}
2sin(\frac{3x}{2})cos(\frac{3x}{2})=sin(3x)
